    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just what people say to make themselves feel better, isn't it? the \"beauty\" is just a chemical reaction in our brains to distract us from the void. if nothing lasts, then nothing actually matters. even the \"connections\" we make are just temporary patterns that disappear. it feels less like a \"purpose\" and more like a trap... just being forced to keep running on a treadmill that leads nowhere.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
